Dated today, from the Court to the Defendant, in response to letters received on August 10, 2016, requesting credit for time served, and on August 15, 2016, requesting a stay of sentence for the birth child. 

Court will grant 19 days of credit. An amended Judgment of Conviction will be prepared. 

Court may grant the request, but would need further proof of pregnancy and due date. If granted, the Court would stay sentence for 48 hours.
